    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#cdl-gwaider1997"/>, pp. 25-29, n. <citedRange>2</citedRange> (with photograph)</bibl>,
                    whence <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2173</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#GVCyr"/> <citedRange>004</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#CEG"/>, n. <citedRange>682</citedRange> (when not yet published)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>39.1723</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.92</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <lg met="dactylic">
                    <l met="hexameter" real="+--|+--|+--|++|+--|++">
                        <lb n="1"/><w lemma="μνῆμα">Mνῆμα</w> <w lemma="ἀρετή">ἀρετῆς</w> <w lemma="ὅδε">τόδε</w> <w lemma="τίθημι">ἔθηκε</w>
                        <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φίλων">Φίλων</name></persName> 
                    <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀρχώι">Ἀρχοῖ</name></persName> <w lemma="συνόμευνος">συνομεύνωι</w>
                    </l>
                    <l met="dactylic">
                        <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="13" unit="character" precision="medium"/><orig><unclear>α</unclear>ι</orig> <gap reason="lost" quantity="5" unit="character" precision="medium"/>
                        <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" atLeast="17" atMost="18" unit="character" precision="medium"/><w part="F">ωι</w>.
                    </l>                
                </lg>
                </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="3">
                        <lem resp="#cdl-gwaider1997"><orig><unclear>α</unclear>ι</orig></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#CEG"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/><orig>ι</orig></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Philôn a fait faire ce <supplied reason="subaudible">monument</supplied> pour son épouse Arkhô comme souvenir de sa valeur <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Philon laid down this <supplied reason="subaudible">monument</supplied> for his wife Archo as a record of her virtue <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Philon pose questa <supplied reason="subaudible">monumento</supplied> per sua moglie Archò in memoria della sua virtù <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The poetic word <foreign xml:lang="grc">συνόμευνος</foreign> is a super-compound based upon two compounds in literary texts: 
                    <foreign xml:lang="grc">σύνευνος</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὅμευνος</foreign>.</p>
                <p>Metrical analysis: the poem was made of one hexameter at text-lines 1-2, followed probably by a pentameter (or another hexameter) now lost 
                    at text-lines 3-4.</p>
             </div></body>
    </text>
